[head=2]Pronouncement[/head][/color]

Station Command Member, by stamping this form, you certify that the justifications for termination that you provided are both reasonable and true, and you assert that the employee is unfit for duty in their original department. From this order, the employee is unable to be hired in the same department for at least seven days, any applications to that department should be automatically denied by the Head of Personnel. Applications to other departments can be accepted, but input should be given to the Department Head of the department being applied for, to consider the original justifications for the employee being fired.

[bold]Protected Groups[/bold]
An employee can NOT be fired on the basis of race, national or ethnic origin, color, species, religion, age, gender identity, sexual orientation, pregnancy, familial status, disability, veteran status, or genetic information.


[color=RoyalBlue]──────────────────────────────────────[/color]

[color=Gray]This form requires a stamp from the Head of Personnel, as well as either the head of the department of employment, or the Captain.[/color]
